com.algodeal.marketrunner.orders.implementations
Class TransactionDetails

java.lang.Object
  com.algodeal.marketrunner.orders.implementations.TransactionDetails
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class TransactionDetails
extends Object
implements Serializable

All the information that describe a transaction. If several transactions have occurred simultaneously (from the point of view of the strategy), then all their details are cumulated into a single object (so there would be a single callback done).

Method Detail

getDate

public org.joda.time.DateTime getDate()
Returns the date when the transaction occurred. If there has been several simultaneous transactions from the point of view of the strategy, it is possible (but very rare) that they have different (and very close) dates. In this case, this is the date of the last transaction.

getPrice

public double getPrice()
Returns the price paid for each share or contract for this transaction. If there has been several simultaneous transactions for the same order, then this is the average price paid.

getExecutedQuantity

public long getExecutedQuantity()
Returns the number of shares or contracts for this transaction, or the sum of the shares of all accumulated transactions if there has been several simultaneous transactions for the same order.

getValue

public double getValue()
Returns the value of this transaction, or the sum of the values of all accumulated transactions if there has been several simultaneous transactions for the same order.

getTransactionCosts

public double getTransactionCosts()
Returns the costs of this transaction, or the sum of the costs of all accumulated transactions if there has been several simultaneous transactions for the same order.
